{
  "texts": [
    "In 2017, for example, DarkLight was released in what was then called \"first of its kind\" artificial intelligence tool to enhance cyber security defence [30].",
    "There has since been literature highlighting the beneficial uses of AI in cyber security defence.Early uses of AI in cyber security were based around developing discriminative-based machine learning (ML) or deep learning (DL) AI models.",
    "ML tools are capable of discriminating data through classifying information, and recognising specific patterns [31].",
    "Though powerful, ML is also limited in terms of threat detection as it acts according to pre-defined features, meaning that any features not pre-defined will evade detection [31].",
    "DL models, a subset of ML, on the other hand are able to learn high-level abstract characteristics, or deeper features of given data, making them excel at things like image and speech recognition, text analysis and natural language processing [32]."
  ]
}